&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Real Estate &amp;amp; Workplace (REW) Facilities Site Manager will lead Databricks’ EMEA operations from our London office, overseeing sites across Paris, Munich, Stockholm, Israel, Zurich and Riyadh. You’ll play a key role in shaping and executing workplace strategies that enable Databricks’ rapid regional growth and deliver exceptional employee experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to scale our EMEA workplace support model, strengthen key vendor partnerships, and ensure operational excellence across a growing portfolio supporting over 1,000 Bricksters — with continued expansion ahead. The role reports to the International Real Estate &amp;amp; Workplace Leader and may include occasional travel to regional offices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact you will have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver the best in class service for employees, customers and investors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage support team for internal events/training/hackdays as well as company happy hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee front of house activities such as: security management, food and beverage programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide all facilities and workplace operations to achieve an exceptional environment which manifests and deepens company culture in our workplaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross functionally with your extended International REW&amp;nbsp; team supporting projects and programs within the scope of Workplace and Real Estate Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a coverage model that supports day to day facilities requests are completed - work as a part of REW team to follow standards and key measures to ensure a consistent level of support&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong relationships with internal stakeholders (EA’s, team leaders) and partner teams (HR, IT, Finance and property management) as well as external vendor services to ensure highest quality solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on special projects as a part of the global REW team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop, improve and document consistent operational processes such as: Oversee regular office maintenance programs- janitorial, patch &amp;amp; paint and safety equipment etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize and document operational processes: OpEx, CapEx, Security and Safety Programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years management experience with responsibility for operations and service delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building schedules, coverage models and working with cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills and the ability to draft office communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven organizational skills, managing multiple work streams and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer focussed attitude - ensuring consistently high quality resolutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial and budget experience; including sourcing/procuring goods or services and following procurement best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working and managing projects within a distributed, remote environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
