&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Account Executive - Public Sector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Public Sector Account Executive – Japan, you will own strategic sales into Japan’s government and broader public sector, driving adoption of our data and AI platform across central ministries, local governments, and public institutions.&amp;nbsp;You will lead the full sales cycle, build executive relationships, and collaborate closely with internal and partner teams to support Japan’s digital government and modernization initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The impact you will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and exceed revenue targets by winning new public sector customers across Japan, including central ministries, local governments, government agencies, and public institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a clear territory and account strategy to identify, prioritize, and win high‑potential public sector accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, document, and drive the expansion of Databricks usage in newly landed accounts, turning initial projects into broad, high‑impact data and AI platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify new AI and data use cases in government operations and feed these insights into Japan’s public sector go‑to‑market, influencing product direction and regional strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use a solution‑oriented, value‑based sales approach that links Databricks to measurable outcomes for public services and citizens.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orchestrate Databricks’ internal teams and our ecosystem of partners (SI, cloud, and consulting partners) to run effective sales motions and deliver successful customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we look for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of SaaS, cloud, AI, or big data sales experience in Japan, with meaningful exposure to public sector accounts and a proven ability to drive adoption of new technologies through a consultative, solutions‑oriented sales approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to navigate complex public sector stakeholder ecosystems, building consensus across multiple departments, budget owners, and decision/approval layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of public sector priorities in Japan, including typical buying processes, buying cycles, decision‑making structures, and the broader ecosystem of partners that support government projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience with Japanese government procurement, including familiarity with budget formulation and execution, tender/RFP processes, evaluation criteria, and relevant compliance and security frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in selling usage‑based PaaS/SaaS or data, AI, and ML solutions is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid experience applying structured sales methodologies and processes (e.g., account planning, MEDDPICC, value selling, Command of the Message) to win complex, multi‑stakeholder deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of creating strong customer champions and leading collaborative internal and external teams to support implementation and expansion within strategic accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear understanding of how to build a focused partner strategy for the public sector and manage SI, cloud, and consulting partners to jointly win and deliver large, impactful projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
