&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;SLSQ226R312&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an EBC Manager at Databricks, you will be a strategic leader responsible for designing, delivering, and continuously improving high-impact executive briefing experiences for our most important customers and prospects. You will manage the end-to-end EBC program at your site, curate tailored content and agendas, and serve as a trusted advisor to both internal teams and C-level customer stakeholders. This is a highly cross-functional role, requiring close collaboration with Sales, Field Engineering, Product, Marketing, and Facilities to drive business outcomes, accelerate product adoption, and deepen executive relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will thrive in our fast-paced, collaborative, and metrics-driven culture, where creativity, technical acumen, and a customer-first mindset are essential. If you are passionate about shaping transformative customer experiences and influencing strategic sales opportunities, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EBC Program Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and scale the EBC program at your site, including demand generation, agenda coordination, content curation, and success reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain best practices, playbooks, and operational frameworks for consistent, high-quality delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Facilities and vendors to ensure seamless logistics, venue setup, and hospitality for on-site briefings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain an understanding of various partner offerings that enhance the Datrabricks portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep up to date with the developments in Datrabricks solutions through training and collaborating closely with product, field engineering, and enablement teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on-site EBCs with customers to ensure they are delivering the ideal customer experience and executed with quality leadership by the account team and content delivery by speakers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Briefing Planning &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the planning, organization, and execution of executive briefings for high-value customers, ensuring each engagement is tailored to business needs and sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise account teams on strategy, content, speakers, demos, and best practices to maximize the impact of each EBC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead EBC engagement strategy/calls to gain an understanding of goals and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend / advise on the right strategy and approach, including appropriate EBC agenda content that comprehensively covers Databricks solutions to address customer needs and target business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop tailored insights and use data/conduct research specific to each account to inform the selection of topics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehend the customer business needs and problems addressed by Datrabricks&#39; solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content Development &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product, Marketing, and Field Engineering to develop compelling, business-outcome-focused briefing materials, including presentations, demos, and case studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver engaging presentations to executive audiences, adapting messaging to industry, vertical, and customer priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Engagement &amp;amp; Relationship Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for customers throughout the briefing process, building trust and fostering long-term relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and synthesize customer feedback and insights, sharing actionable recommendations with internal teams to inform product and sales strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous Improvement &amp;amp; Sales Support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze EBC outcomes and customer feedback to identify gaps, recommend improvements, and evolve content offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Executive Engagement team in enhancing demo and content libraries, and develop repeatable best practices for effective customer engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback and coaching to account teams and speakers for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Executive Engagement team leadership in enhancing and improving our content and demo offerings based on customer feedback and observations in EBCs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and recommend solutions for gaps in the EBC content offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the impact of EBC agendas and develop repeatable best practices for delivering effective customer engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Look For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in executive briefings, meetings management, sales enablement or high-touch B2B customer engagement as an Account Executive or Solutions Architect within a technology or enterprise software company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage complex programs and multiple concurrent projects in a fast-paced, high-growth environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with experience presenting to and engaging with C-level executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical aptitude and the ability to quickly learn and communicate the value of Databricks’ solutions portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience advising on and developing business-outcome-focused content and agendas for executive audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly collaborative, with a track record of working cross-functionally with Sales, Product, Marketing, and Operations teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management, organizational, and analytical skills; metrics-driven and detail-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-centric mindset with a passion for delivering world-class experiences and building trusted relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative problem solver and self-starter, comfortable with ambiguity and change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Google Suite, MS Excel, PowerPoint, and meeting management tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel as needed to support EBCs and executive events in key locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
